    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type of moss commonly found in the southern United States, characterized by tufts of grey strands on the trunks and branches of trees. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
